{
  "id": "mini-project",
  "courseId": "javascript-fundamentals",
  "title": "Mini project: Habit tracker",
  "description": "Use everything you've learned to build a small habit tracker from scratch.",
  "order": 10,
  "language": "javascript",
  "estimatedMinutes": 30,
  "objectives": [
    "Model a small data structure with arrays and objects",
    "Split the program into small, testable functions",
    "Wire the functions together in `main()` and print a summary"
  ],
  "teachesConceptTags": [
    "modeling-state",
    "composing-functions"
  ],
  "usesConceptTags": [
    "function-declaration",
    "parameters",
    "return",
    "arrays",
    "array-methods",
    "objects",
    "property-access",
    "for-loop",
    "comparison",
    "template-literals",
    "console-log"
  ],
  "completionRules": [
    {
      "type": "required_file_contains",
      "file": "main.js",
      "pattern": "function addHabit"
    },
    {
      "type": "required_file_contains",
      "file": "main.js",
      "pattern": "function markDone"
    },
    {
      "type": "required_file_contains",
      "file": "main.js",
      "pattern": "function summary"
    },
    {
      "type": "function_tests",
      "tests": [
        {
          "name": "addHabit creates entry",
          "call": "addHabit([], \"read\")",
          "expected": "[{\"name\": \"read\", \"done\": false}]"
        },
        {
          "name": "addHabit appends",
          "call": "addHabit([{\"name\": \"read\", \"done\": false}], \"walk\")",
          "expected": "[{\"name\": \"read\", \"done\": false}, {\"name\": \"walk\", \"done\": false}]"
        },
        {
          "name": "markDone flips a habit",
          "call": "markDone([{\"name\": \"read\", \"done\": false}, {\"name\": \"walk\", \"done\": false}], \"walk\")",
          "expected": "[{\"name\": \"read\", \"done\": false}, {\"name\": \"walk\", \"done\": true}]"
        },
        {
          "name": "markDone unknown name leaves list alone",
          "call": "markDone([{\"name\": \"read\", \"done\": false}], \"nope\")",
          "expected": "[{\"name\": \"read\", \"done\": false}]",
          "hidden": true
        },
        {
          "name": "summary none done",
          "call": "summary([{\"name\": \"read\", \"done\": false}, {\"name\": \"walk\", \"done\": false}])",
          "expected": "\"0 of 2 habits done\""
        },
        {
          "name": "summary some done",
          "call": "summary([{\"name\": \"read\", \"done\": true}, {\"name\": \"walk\", \"done\": false}])",
          "expected": "\"1 of 2 habits done\""
        },
        {
          "name": "summary all done",
          "call": "summary([{\"name\": \"a\", \"done\": true}, {\"name\": \"b\", \"done\": true}])",
          "expected": "\"2 of 2 habits done\"",
          "hidden": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "expected_stdout",
      "expected": "read: todo\nwalk: done\nmeditate: todo\n1 of 3 habits done"
    }
  ],
  "prerequisiteLessonIds": ["objects-basics"],
  "recap": "You modeled a list of habits as an array of `{ name, done }` objects, wrote small functions to add and update them, and composed those functions in `main()`. That split — data + small functions + a main that wires them together — is how every larger program is built.",
  "practicePrompts": [
    "Add a `removeHabit(habits, name)` function that returns a new array without the matching entry.",
    "Add a `pending(habits)` function that returns only the habits that aren't done yet."
  ],
  "practiceExercises": []
}
